<HEADLINE> World Population Day Observed in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 11 (Xinhua) -- World Population Day was observed in
Bangladesh Tuesday with a well-timed theme "Saving Women's Life",
giving due importance to curbing the birth rate in the greater
socio-economic interest of the country.
</P>
<P>
To mark the day, various programs have been chalked out at
national, district and upazila (county) levels.
</P>
<P>
A discussion and prize-giving ceremony were held at Shishu
Academy in the morning, at which Health and Family Welfare
Minister Sheikh Fazlul Karim Selim distributed prizes to 12 best
family welfare assistants, six non-governmental organizations, one
union health and family welfare center and a mother and child
welfare center for their remarkable contributions to family
planning programs.
</P>
<P>
On the occasion, President Shahabuddin Ahmed and Prime Minister
Sheikh Hasina issued separate messages, stressing the need for
coordinated efforts toward ensuring safe life of women and
building a planned family life for an all-out development of the
country.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister said in her message that the birth rate in
the country has declined from 3 percent to 1.5 percent, expressing
the hope to build two-kids family by the year 2005. 
</P>
</TEXT>
