<HEADLINE> Xinhua Middle East News Summary at 2000 GMT, Wednesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran has closed down its 725-kilometer borders with
eastern neighbor Afghanistan as part of the measures to combat
threats to its security.
</P>
<P>
The move was taken on Tuesday during a visit by Interior
Minister Abdolvahed Mousavi Lari to the eastern parts of the
country in northeastern province of Khorasan following a sharp rise
in criminal cases of robbery, kidnaps, murders and drug trafficking
in the border regions.
</P>
<P>
"With the eastern borders fully controlled, the residents will
enjoy full tranquility and security," Lari told the Islamic
Republic News Agency during his inspection tour. (Iran-
Afghanistan-Border Closure)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- The General Workers Confederation (GWC) of Lebanon and
10 political groups of the country launched a demonstration in
Beirut Wednesday afternoon to protest against the government's
financial and social policies.
</P>
<P>
The demonstration would be the biggest against the current
government since it was installed 20 months ago, local Al Mustaqbal
newspaper said before the start of the demonstration.
</P>
<P>
The GWC, which groups Lebanon's 350,000-strong labor force, had
called on the demonstrators to assemble at 5 p.m. (1400 GMT) to
converge on the cabinet headquarters when the 16-member cabinet
under Prime Minister Salim Hoss would hold its regular weekly
session.(Lebanon-Demonstration)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- U.N. Middle East envoy Terje Roed-Larsen said
Wednesday that the U.N. peacekeepers can be deployed throughout
south Lebanon at the end of this month once Israel has made
required changes of its troops' deployment on the border.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with Israeli Foreign Minister David Levy here,
Larsen said it was hard to say exactly when the peacekeeping troops
would deploy in south Lebanon "because we are waiting for all
Israeli violations to come to an end."
</P>
<P>
Israel pulled all its forces out of south Lebanon on May 24,
ending its 22-year occupation of the land there. However, the U.N.
Interim Force in Lebanon (UNIFIL) has not deployed in the vacated
areas as Beirut still claims that Israel is violating its
sovereignty at nine points on the border. (Israel-Lebanon-Border)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY -- Kuwaiti National Assembly (parliament) on
Wednesday approved the maritime border agreement with Saudi Arabia
signed earlier this month, the official KUNA news agency reported.
All 53 parliamentarians and cabinet ministers present at the ballot
voted in favor of the agreement, which had already been approved by
the Kuwaiti cabinet on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia approved the pact earlier this week.
</P>
<P>
The accord was signed in the Kuwaiti capital by Kuwaiti Foreign
Minister Sabah Al-Jaber Al-Sabah and his Saudi counterpart Saud Al-
Faisal on July 2 during a visit to Kuwait by Saudi Crown Prince
Abdullah Ibn Abdul-Aziz. (Kuwait-Parliament-Maritime Pact)
</P>
</TEXT>
