<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Officer Sentenced to Jail for Selling State Secrets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Russia on Wednesday sentenced Lt.
Col. Avramenko, an officer of the Russian Defense Ministry's
Central Research Center, to four years in jail on the charge of
intending to sell military secrets to foreign intelligence
agencies.
</P>
<P>
"The spy, Lt. Col. Avramenko, was exposed by the Federal
Security Service (FSB)'s Military Counterintelligence Department.
The Moscow District Military Court has sentenced him to four years
in a high-security prison on charges of state treason stipulated
in Article 275 of the Criminal Code," the FSB Public Relations
Center announced here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"It has been established that Avramenko, motivated by selfish
goals and making use of his official position, had collected
secret materials about the latest developments in aircraft
building and the future of the Russian air force and made
photocopies of these materials," said the center.
</P>
<P>
"While abroad in May 1996, Avramenko tried to sell those
materials to representatives of a foreign state for a large reward,
" it said.
</P>
<P>
"The materials about the Russian air force collected by
Avramenko were of great interest to the foreign special services
and their leak might have seriously damaged Russia's state
security," noted the center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
