<HEADLINE> Greek, Luxembourg FMs Urge Turkey to Make Constructive Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, July 12 (Xinhua) -- The foreign ministers of Greece
and Luxembourg Wednesday called for constructive efforts by Turkey
to help itself to join the European Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
Speaking after their talks focusing on bilateral ties, the
Cyprus issue and Greek-Turkish relations as well as EU-Turkish
relations, George Papandreou of Greece and Lydie Polfer of
Luxembourg said that there must be constructive efforts on behalf
of Turkey in order to proceed with the necessary reforms that
would contribute to Ankara's European course.
</P>
<P>
Papandreou said that Greece wanted a more European vocation
for Turkey and any progress to be made during the currently Geneva
talks between Cyprus' two communities would definitely assist
Turkey's European course within the framework of the Helsinki
decisions.
</P>
<P>
Describing the relations between the two countries as"
excellent," Polfer, who is on a visit to Greece, said that Greece
and Luxembourg shared almost the same views over the issues of
Cyprus and Greek-Turkish relations.
</P>
<P>
She said that the Helsinki EU summit decisions and the
Copenhagen criteria should serve as a basis for Turkey to proceed
with the necessary steps towards reform and good-neighborly
relations with its neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
she called the recent Strovilia incident within the cease-fire
line on Cyprus an "unexpected" development, saying that it was a "
wrong move at the wrong time." 
</P>
</TEXT>
