<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romanian Beer Market Grows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 12 (Xinhua) -- The estimated beer consumption
this year in Romania will be 12 million hectoliters, the official
Rompres news agency informed on Wednesday citing sources in
Romania's Brewers Association.
</P>
<P>
Although the beer consumption in Romania is one third of the
consumption that is registered in the European developed countries,
however the Romanian brewers say the domestic beer market is
continuously developing. They estimate a consumption of 14.5
million hectoliters of beer in 2005.
</P>
<P>
Sales in 2000 were influenced by the European Soccer
Championship in June, when beer consumption in Romania increased
by 24 percent as against the previous month.
</P>
<P>
There are over 70 breweries in Romania, of which 52 have a
small capacity and they belong to local brewers. After 1990,
Romanian breweries attracted investments worth 575 million U.S.
dollars. Some well-known international companies such as Brau
Union, Pilsener, Tuborg Stella Artois, Keiser have penetrated the
Romanian market.
</P>
<P>
These companies supply about 50 percent of the beer production
in Romania.
</P>
<P>
In 1999, the total consumption of alcoholic drinks in Romania
was 92 liters per capita, the beer being 58.76 percent of this
quantity. The consumption of wine, a traditional drink in Romania,
was 28.2 percent only last year, statistics show. 
</P>
</TEXT>
