<HEADLINE> Annan Appoints New Force Commander for UNTAET </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 12 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan on Wednesday appointed Lieutenant-General Boonsrang
Niumpradit of Thailand as Force Commander of the Military
component of the United Nations Transitional Administration in
East Timor(UNTAET) with effect from July 19, 2000.
</P>
<P>
 He will succeed Lieutenant-General Jaime de los Santos of the
Philippines, who will return to his national service.
</P>
<P>
 Lieutenant-General Niumpradit joined the Thai Armed forces in
1963. He received his military training at the Armed Forces
Academies Preparatory School in Thailand and later attended the
Chulachomklao Royal Military Academy as well as the United States
Military Academy.
</P>
<P>
On August 30, 1999, the people of East Timor voted by means of
a direct, secret and universal ballot to begin a process leading
towards independence.
</P>
<P>
UNTAET was established to administer the territory and
exercise legislative and executive authority during the transition
period.
</P>
<P>
UNTAET consults and works in close cooperation with the East
Timorese people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
