<HEADLINE> German War Reparations Issue Must Be Solved at Political Level, Says Reppas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 12 (Xinhua) -- The issue of the German war
reparations must be solved at a political level because of its
sensitiveness, said Greek government spokesman Dimitris Reppas
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press briefing, Reppas said that the Greek
government was opposed to the decision made by the relatives of
the victims of the massacred Distomo villagers whom Germany
refuses to compensate.
</P>
<P>
The issue was a sensitive one and such issues were being dealt
with taking under consideration the national interest without
ignoring the interests of the people based on the decision reached
by the Greek court, he said.
</P>
<P>
He confirmed that the German government made protest demarches
in response to the confiscation of German property procedure that
is underway in Athens for the compensation of the victims'
relatives.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman reaffirmed that the approval of the justice
minister was needed in order to proceed with the confiscation of a
foreign state property.
</P>
<P>
Despite the Greek government's opposition, some court
officials Tuesday started recording the German Goethe Institute's
property in Athens as part of their efforts to confiscate the
three German cultural institutions in Athens in order to raise a
sum of 9.5 billion drachmas (about 27 million U.S. dollars) to pay
for the relatives of the 218 villagers of Distomo, near Delphi,
massacred by German occupations forces on June 10, 1944. 
</P>
