<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mekong River Commission Discusses Environment Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 12 (Xinhua) -- The Mekong River Commission (MRC)
held a regional consultative conference on the 2001-2005
environment program in Ho Chi Minh City on July 10-12, Vietnam
News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The conference, the second of its kind, had the participation
of Vietnam, Thailand, Laos and Cambodia and discussed the
environment program aimed at achieving the MRC's targets for
Mekong River management and usage.
</P>
<P>
Participants at the conference approved the aims of the program,
which will improve the capability to monitor and evaluate the
environment of the river basin, raise awareness of regional
environmental issues, strengthen the exchange of environment
information, improve environmental policies and regulations
relating to the management of water and other resources.
</P>
<P>
The conference also agreed to increase knowledge and capacity
to assess environmental problems and improve coordination in the
development of the Mekong river basin.
</P>
<P>
The program will be carried out at an estimated cost of 24
million U.S. dollars mobilized by MRC from various financial
sources.
</P>
<P>
MRC will arrange national workshops in August and September
2000 to discuss measures to implement the program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
