<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 7 Killed in Party Conflict in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Five mid-ranking Bangladesh Chhatra
League (Bangladesh Students' League) leaders and two drivers were
shot dead by gunmen Wednesday at Bahaddarhat in Chittagong, the
largest port city in the country, the United News of Bangladesh (
UNB)reported.
</P>
<P>
Police said a group of gunmen of Islami Chhatra Shibir (Islami
Students' Front) riding a black micro-bus sprayed bullets on
another micro-bus carrying the victims at about 11:30 am.
</P>
<P>
Five of them died on the spot and two at the Chittagong Medical
College Hospital. Five others with bullet wounds were admitted to
the hospital.
</P>
<P>
Sharply reacting to the killing, angry Bangladesh Chhatra
League(BCL) workers ransacked Bakulia and Kalamia Bazar,
strongholds of the Islami Chhatra Shibir (ICS).
</P>
<P>
The BCL also held an impromptu protest rally at Andarkilla
where they clashed with the ICS, leaving several people injured.
</P>
<P>
Metropolitan Police Commissioner of Chittagong Ahmedul Huq told
the UNB that Wednesday's bloody incident might be a sequel to long-
running conflict between the BCL and the ICS.
</P>
<P>
The BCL central leader Simanta Talukdar accused the ICS of
staging the massacre, threatening that if the killers are not
arrested within 24 hours, the BCL will announce action program
Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
