<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 32 Bangladeshis Killed by Indian BSF in Last 6 Months: BDR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Border Security Force (BSF) of India
has killed 32 Bangladesh nationals and injured another 42 during
the last six months, Bangladesh Rifles (BDR) headquarters said
here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A senior BDR official said during the period, the BSF kidnapped
111 Bangladeshis and released them later after torture. The BSF
also pushed 46 Bengali-speaking Indian citizens into Bangladesh
through different borders, he added.
</P>
<P>
Firing continued Wednesday between the BDR and the BSF at
Sylhet and Kurigram frontiers following the killing of three
Bangladeshis by the BSF within the span of 24 hours on Monday and
Tuesday morning, official Bangladesh News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
A large number of people were evacuated from Bangladesh's
border areas as tension mounted there following the firing
incidents.
</P>
<P>
"Bangladesh Rifles has been asked to prevent any further
attacks from the BSF," the BDR official said, adding that the BDR
has also been asked to remain alert along the 4123-kilometer
borders.
</P>
<P>
On Monday morning, the BSF opened fire at some Bangladeshi
laborers who were engaged in stone collection in a frontier river
and left a young man dead on the spot.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday morning, the BSF once again brutally killed two
brothers who were ploughing their lands at Kurigram frontiers
inside Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
"In most cases, the BSF used to kill our people without any
provocation," alleged the BDR official. 
</P>
</TEXT>
