<HEADLINE> ASEAN Trade Union Leaders Conference Held in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 12 (Xinhua) -- A conference of ASEAN Trade Union
Council leaders opened here Wednesday, discussing a plan of action
for the trade union movement of ASEAN countries, according to a
report of Vietnam News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The two-day conference, hosted by the Vietnam General
Confederation of Labour (VGCL), drew 20 delegates from the trade
organizations of Vietnam, Singapore, Malaysia, the Philippines,
Indonesia Thailand and Laos.
</P>
<P>
Participants reviewed the implementation of the 1997 Bali
Declaration, dealing with such issues as job creation, minimum
wage, trade unions' policies in overcoming the impact of the
regional financial crisis, and making a plan of action for the
trade union movement in the context of rapid globalization.
</P>
<P>
The conference, held for the first time in Vietnam since the
country became an official member of the ASEAN Trade Union Council
(ATUC in November, 1997, also passed a resolution to admit the Lao
Trade Unions' Organization to the ASEAN Trade Union Council as its
eighth official member. 
</P>
