<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 12 (Xinhua) -- The Government of the Federal
Republic of Germany has agreed to provide Nepal a grant assistance
worth of 20.5 million U.S. dollars, Nepali Finance Ministry said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
An agreement on the grant assistance was signed here Wednesday
between the governments, said the ministry.
</P>
<P>
