<HEADLINE> Burundi Peace Agreement to be Signed Soon: Mandela </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Former South African
president Nelson Mandela said here Wednesday that Burundi's 19
political parties would sign an agreement in Arusha, Tanzania, on
July 20.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was aimed at achieving a lasting peace for the
central African nation.
</P>
<P>
The chief negotiator in the Burundi peace process told
reporters at his Johannesburg home that he was optimistic that the
agreement would be concluded without any interference.
</P>
<P>
"All stakeholders have decided that when the facilitation team
comes out with the final process they will accept it," said
Mandela, who became a peace broker in the Burundi conflict late
last year.
</P>
<P>
But he urged all political parties to represent the issues of
the Burundian people.
</P>
<P>
"We will take the parties into Burundi so that they can speak to
people and fairly represent them and not put across their own
philosophical views," Mandela said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
