<HEADLINE> Russia Strives for Normalizing Korean Peninsula Situation: Putin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Russia supports the normalization
of relations between the Democratic People's Republic of Korea(
DPRK) and the Republic of Korea (RK) and will do everything to
promote this process, said Russian President Vladimir Putin on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"Russia has traditionally friendly relations with the DPRK. I
regret that no leader of either Russia or the former Soviet Union
ever paid an official visit to this country," Putin told an
interview with Russia's ORT television, Japan's NHK television and
the Reuters news agency on the eve of his departure for Pyongyang.
</P>
<P>
"First, we have many bilateral issues. Second, we want to
discuss a number of international issues, including those related
to security, with the leader of the DPRK," Putin said.
</P>
<P>
The Russian president also noted that he had recently spoken by
phone with the president of the Republic of Korea. "We agreed that
I will pay a visit to South Korea as well," he said.
</P>
<P>
"The Democratic People's Republic of Korea is our neighbor, we
have a common border. We are very interested in the restoration of
peace and accord on the Korean Peninsula, as this directly
reflects on Russia," Putin stressed.
</P>
<P>
"This is the third complex of issues that we are going to
discuss with the DPRK leadership," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We have no doubt that this will give a good impulse to the
development of bilateral relations," Putin predicted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
