<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan to Block Internet Telephony, Porn Websites </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan has decided to block
Internet telephony and pornographic websites, for the interests of
the nation, the Associated Press of Pakistan reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
To this effect, the Pakistan Telecommunication Company Limited
(PTCL) is establishing two National Access Points NAP) in Karachi
and Islamabad to achieve the monitoring of exiting circuits,
traffic analysis and effective utilization of the Internet
bandwidth.
</P>
<P>
Telephone calls made via Internet have caused a huge revenue
loss to PTCL estimated to be in the range of 2.8 million U.S.
dollars per annum.
</P>
<P>
The NAP will enable the PTCL to effectively block all vice
telephony over Internet and the subscribers will not be able to
access the websites like media ring, dialpad.com and hottelephone.
com.
</P>
<P>
Besides, blocking the voice the NAP will also allow the PTCL to
control asymmetrical solution and frame relay function.
</P>
</TEXT>
