<HEADLINE> Pepsi Builds Division in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Pepsi Cola Co. has established
another division in China, the Tianjin Pepsi-Cola Beverage Co.,
formally launched Tuesday in this north China municipality.
</P>
<P>
The joint-venture, set up with approval from the State Economic
and Trade Commission, is the second-ranking world soft drink giant
division in Tianjin after Coca Cola.
</P>
<P>
Scheduled to be completed in mid-2001, the new plant will
produce carbonated beverages with the Pepsi brand and some Chinese
brand soft drinks.
</P>
<P>
Pepsi Co. Investment (China) Ltd. and Tianjin Development
Holding Co., Ltd. each will hold 44 percent shares of stock, and
Tianjin Economic and Technological Development Company will hold
the remaining 12 percent.
</P>
<P>
The 150 million yuan (18 million US dollars) joint-venture will
be spread over an area of 60,000 square meters in the Tianjin
Economic and Technological Zone.  
</P>
</TEXT>
