<HEADLINE> Construction of Large Hydropower Station Starts in Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHADA (TIBET), July 12 (Xinhua) -- Construction on a large
hydropower station in Tibet started today in Ngari prefecture, in
the western part of the Tibet Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The hydropower station, located three kilometers from Zhada
county in the prefecture, is the largest in the Ngari.
</P>
<P>
According to Zhao Xingwei, head of the project, the installed
capacity of the station will reach 800 kilowatts, and the yearly
energy output will be 5.66 million kilowatt hours.
</P>
<P>
The station will be finished in two years, and the first set
400-kilowatt work unit will begin to generate electricity by the
end of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
