<HEADLINE> Sapling Breeding Base Built in Beijing Suburbs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Construction of a large-scale
modern sapling breeding base began today in Beijing's northern
suburb of Changping, in an effort to provide more green in the
areas surrounding the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
The state-level 60.79-million-yuan (7.32 million US dollars)
breeding base is believed the largest in the country.
</P>
<P>
It is made up of 30,000 square meters of air-conditioned rooms,
23 hectares of seedling nursery and storage, and 100 hectares of
irrigated planting area.
</P>
<P>
After completion, the base is likely to provide 16 million
saplings, which will give a big boost to environmental protection
work near Beijing and in northern China.
</P>
<P>
This spring Beijing was besieged by sandstorms and now
sweltering temperatures are the norm.
</P>
<P>
Analysts attribute the problems to the lack of plants and poor
soil and water conservation in the areas around the capital.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
