<HEADLINE> Air China Plane Veers Off Runway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 12 (Xinhua) -- A Boeing-737 passenger plane
scheduled to fly to Beijing veered off a runway at the Pudong
International Airport at 12:59 today, but the more than 160 crew
and passengers were all reported safe, sources said.
</P>
<P>
The airport was closed temporarily and some international and
domestic arrivals and departures were transferred to the Hongqiao
International Airport.
</P>
<P>
By 16:14, the plane had been towed away for check up and the
airport resumed operation.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident is under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
