<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northwest Chinese Province Starts Party, Government Bodies Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, July 12 (Xinhua) -- The reform of party and government
bodies at the provincial level was formerly kicked off today in
northwest China's Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
According to the scheme announced here today, the number of
provincial party and government departments will be reduced from
67 to 60.
</P>
<P>
Staffs of the provincial committee of the party will be cut by
20 percent, those of the provincial government by 50 percent, and
law enforcement agencies by 27 percent.
</P>
<P>
The reform will also lead to a noticeable drop in the average
age of key officials, said Ai Peishan, Shaanxi's deputy party
chief. 
</P>
</TEXT>
