<HEADLINE> Major Chemicals Producer Lists Stock on Shanghai Bourse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 12 (Xinhua) -- The A share stock of Nanning
Chemicals, a major alkali producer in China, was listed on the
Shanghai Stock Exchange today.
</P>
<P>
In August 1998, the company based in Nanning, capital of
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region in southwest China, issued the
country's first convertible corporate bond, raising 150 million
yuan for its technical upgrading projects.
</P>
<P>
In June this year, it issued 40 million shares of common stocks,
raising a further 186 million yuan for fine chemical and
biochemical projects.
</P>
<P>
According to company sources, from today through August 2003
when the bond matures, investors may convert their corporate bonds
into common stocks of the company at a discount. 
</P>
</TEXT>
