<HEADLINE> Youth Federation to Promote Technology Innovation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 12 (Xinhua) -- The All-China Youth Federation (
ACYF) will further promote technology innovation to accelerate
economic development, ACYF chairman Bayin Chaolu said here today.
</P>
<P>
He mapped out the federation's five-year plan at the First
Plenum of ACYF's Ninth National Committee.
</P>
<P>
As young people are a driving force in China's technology
innovation, he said ACYF will guide and organize them to get more
involved in the country's economic development.
</P>
<P>
He said the ACYF should serve as a bridge between colleges and
enterprises to integrate research and production, and promote the
economic cooperation between the developed east and underdeveloped
west.
</P>
<P>
Mentioning young people studying abroad in particular, he said,
"They are emotionally attached to the homeland and we should help
them to participate in China's development."
</P>
<P>
As for the government's strategy of developing the west, he
said the ACYF should continue organizing groups of Ph.D.s and
young entrepreneurs to work and invest in the western areas.
</P>
</TEXT>
