<HEADLINE> New Bus Route Between Bangladesh, India to be Surveyed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 12 (Xinhua) -- An Indian government delegation will
arrive here on July 18 to survey possible routes to open Dhaka-
Agartala bus service, the second road traffic with Bangladesh, a
Communication Ministry source said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The delegation led by a joint secretary of the Indian Ministry
of Communication will follow up the meeting held in Delhi last
month, at which a Bangladesh team held preliminary talks with an
Indian team.
</P>
<P>
The first direct road communication between the two neighboring
countries has already been established with introduction of bus
service between Calcutta and Dhaka in June last year.
</P>
<P>
The source said the agreed minutes of the Delhi meeting will be
discussed in Dhaka. On July 18 and 19 the two sides will visit the
possible routes to be selected for commencing the direct bus
service between Dhaka and Agartala, the capital of northeastern
Indian State of Tripura.
</P>
<P>
They will also see the infrastructure facilities before giving
a green signal to open the second road communication between the
two neighboring countries after Dhaka-Calcutta bus service which
has successfully run for a year. 
</P>
