<HEADLINE> Estrada: MILF's Declaration of Jihad Unwarranted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph Estrada
called Wednesday the declaration of jihad by Chairman Hashim
Salamat of the Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF) as unwarranted,
saying that the government has not declared war against the Muslim
people.
</P>
<P>
the president said he had only ordered government troops to
step up efforts in running after MILF rebels "who have violated
the ceasefire agreement or committed other criminal or illegal
acts."
</P>
<P>
The president was reacting to the call by Salamat for his
people to rise in jihad or armed struggle against the government,
after the fall of Camp Abubakar, MILF's main headquarters in
Mindanao, to government hands last Sunday.
</P>
<P>
He said he regretted that the military's decisive victory
against the Muslim separatist rebels has prompted the MILF
leadership to declare a war against the people.
</P>
<P>
Estrada said he had hoped that after the fall of Camp Abubakar
and all other MILF camps, the government and the people in
Mindanao could now focus on the more urgent task ahead, which is
to speed up Mindanao's transformation into a regional trade hub
and food-basket of the country.
</P>
<P>
"With the end of hostilities, we had hoped that our Christian
and Muslim brothers alike could now put on fast track our program
to turn the South from a 'land of promise' into a 'land of
fulfillment,'" he said.
</P>
<P>
Estrada also warned rebels who persist in taking up arms
against the government in pursuit of their secessionist cause that
the government "is ready and fully capable of crushing them." To
those who want peace, he said, the government will give them peace.
</P>
</TEXT>
