<HEADLINE> 2nd APEC Youth Science Festival to be Held in Singapore  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 12 (Xinhua) -- The 2nd APEC Youth Science
Festival (AYSF) is to be held in Singapore from July 27 to August
2 with an objective to enhance the intellectual and creative
interests of APEC youths and to provide opportunities for them to
exchange knowledge of science and culture.
</P>
<P>
Chew Tuan Chiong, head of the organizing committee, briefed
the press conference Wednesday that the festival, with Singapore
as its host, will bring together about 600 local and foreign
students, aged between 15 to 18, and about 200 educators from 15
participating nations and regions, namely Australia, Brunei, China,
Hong Kong, Indonesia, Japan, South Korea, Malaysia, New Zealand,
the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand, Chinese Taipei, the United
States and Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
On top of the agenda is a three and half-day science &AMP;
technology exhibition "Better Science, Better World" which will
display innovative scientific investigations carried out by the
students participants in five categories of clean environment,
communications, diversity, interactions and new endeavors.
</P>
<P>
There are also programs for the teacher participants to visit
schools and to participate in science teacher seminar.
</P>
<P>
Chew added that some two million Singapore dollars (about 1.2
million U.S. dollars) have been spent for the festival
preparations.
</P>
<P>
South Korea hosted the first AYSF in 1998 with participation of
some 500 students and teachers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
