<HEADLINE> HK, Mainland Hold Meeting on Commerce, Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 12 (Xinhua) -- The complementary nature of the
advantages of Hong Kong and the Chinese mainland will create
business opportunities and add vitality into the two places,
delegates to a meeting said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Technology Trade and Treaty Law Working Group of the
Chinese Mainland and Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (
HKSAR) Joint Commission on Commerce and Trade held its second
meeting here from July 10 t0 12, 2000.
</P>
<P>
The two sides reviewed the progress of commerce and trade
relations between the two places since the first meeting of the
Joint Commission held in November 1999, as well as extensively
exchanged views over the information exchange and cooperation in
areas of mutual concern.
</P>
<P>
Topics discussed include "enhancing trade through technology"
and "innovation and technology," and technical measures relating
to trade and export control.
</P>
<P>
The two sides briefed their counterparts on the work progress,
relevant policies and implementation details of the Mainland
policy of "enhancing trade through technology" and the strategy of
the HKSAR to adopt more "innovation and technology."
</P>
<P>
It was agreed that both the Mainland and the HKSAR attach great
importance to innovation and technology developments and this was
the driving force for economic development and served as the
foundation for mainland-HKSAR collaboration.
</P>
<P>
The two sides set down the principles for cooperation in
technologies relating to trade. Initial forms of cooperation in
technologies relating to trade had also been agreed.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of the two sides also briefed the meeting on
each other's legal framework for export control and recent
developments, as well as exchanged views on related issues.
</P>
</TEXT>
