<HEADLINE> Center to be Set Up in HK to Enhance Computer Security </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 12 (Xinhua) -- A computer emergency response
center is expected to be set up in Hong Kong to enhance the region
's capacity in handling information security issues.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a seminar on Internet and information security
Wednesday, Acting Director of Information Technology Services
Cheng Yan-chee said the government is fully aware of the
importance of information security.
</P>
<P>
He said effective operation of the team and the center depends
on the joint efforts of and co-operation among IT professionals,
the industry, academics and the local government.
</P>
<P>
"The center will disseminate information and provide inquiry
and helpdesk services when there are information security
incidents," Cheng said.
</P>
<P>
Maintaining communications with similar organizations overseas,
Cheng said the center will collect the latest information on IT
security, and issue alerts on security risks to arouse public
awareness of information security.
</P>
<P>
The government tackles information security issues through the
setting up of a secure infrastructure and a sound legal framework,
as well as promoting public awareness of information security, he
added.
</P>
<P>
To increase public awareness of information security, the
Information Technology Services Department has co-operated with
various agencies in organizing promotional activities such as
seminars to get the message across, the acting director said.
</P>
