<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wrap-up: China Urges U.S. to Abandon NMD (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister Chi
Haotian today urged the United States to treat seriously the
strong appeal of the international community and abandon the
National Missile Defense (NMD) at the earliest time.
</P>
<P>
Chi reiterated the stance of the Chinese government in a
meeting with U.S. Secretary of Defense William Cohen here this
morning.
</P>
<P>
Peace and development are the trend of the time, and the world
is moving toward ease, Chi said.
</P>
<P>
However, the NMD system will have a negative impact on the
efforts for global strategic equilibrium and stability,
international arms control, disarmament and non-proliferation, he
stressed.
</P>
<P>
On the Taiwan issue, Chi said evasion of the One-China
principle has no way out, and Taiwan issue can not and will not be
delayed indefinitely.
</P>
<P>
"China-U.S. relationship is facing opportunities and problems
as well, and the most important and sensitive of the problems is
the Taiwan issue," he said.
</P>
<P>
Pointing out that the U.S. side has promised for many times
its adherence to the One-China policy, observance of the three
China-U.S. joint communiques and the "three-no" commitment, Chi
urged the U.S. to honor its commitment and not to give the Taiwan
authorities a wrong signal.
</P>
<P>
Reunification of China and to oppose splitting activities have
been an irreversible trend and common aspiration of the entire
Chinese people, which has also been favored by people all over the
world, Chi stressed.
</P>
<P>
Cohen said the U.S. side has fully realized the importance and
sensitivity of the Taiwan issue, and it will adhere to the One-
China policy and abide by the three joint communiques between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
On the relations between two armed forces, Chi Haotian voiced
the hope that the U.S. would make efforts in maintaining a healthy
and stable China-U.S. relations so as to create favorable
condition for the development of the military relations of the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Chi said military relations is an important component of China-
U.S. relations. Since early this year, senior officers of the two
armed forces have restored exchanges, and the China-U.S. military
relations have maintained a good momentum of improvement.
</P>
<P>
Cohen said the U.S. side is pleased to see the restoration of
the military relations between the U.S. and China this year, and
the exchanges between senior officers of the two armed forces have
developed smoothly.
</P>
</TEXT>
