<HEADLINE> Wildfires Almost Extinguished in Bulgaria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, July 12 (Xinhua) -- A week-long wave of wildfires
burning across Bulgaria has almost been put out, the official
Bulgarian Telegraph Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The fires, which numbered 523, were caused by a prolonged heat
wave raging throughout the country, damaging vast areas of forest,
crops and houses.
</P>
<P>
In southeast Khaskovo district, over 450,000 acres of farmland
were scorched and 26 houses were burnt down, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria mobilized state and socials resources, including armed
forces and volunteers, to battle the fire in the past week.
</P>
