<HEADLINE> Shaanxi Revamps Irrigation System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Shaanxi province
has invested 130 million yuan (15.7 million US dollars) this year
in revamping its Guanzhong irrigation system.
</P>
<P>
The province made a plan last year to invest a total of 200
million US dollars over the next five years in revamping the
system. World Bank loans totaling 100 million US dollars will
cover half of the investment.
</P>
<P>
According to the plan, some 155 projects will be launched to
improve reservoirs and irrigation canals in the area.
</P>
<P>
So far, 34 such projects have been completed, 1,300 irrigation
canals improved, and about 360,000 families in the area benefited
from the projects.
</P>
<P>
The upgraded irrigation system will cover a total 230,000 ha.
of farmland. As a result, the area's grain output is expected to
rise by as much as 25 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Guanzhong irrigation system irrigates 600,000 ha of
farmland in Shaanxi Province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
