<HEADLINE> Chinese, U.S. Military Leaders on Relations between Two Armed Forces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister Chi
Haotian voiced the hope that the U.S. would make efforts in
maintaining a healthy and stable China-U.S. relations so as to
create favorable condition for the development of the military
relations of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Chi made the remarks here today when meeting with U.S.
Secretary of Defense William Cohen.
</P>
<P>
Chi said military relations is an important component of China-
U.S. relations. Since early this year, senior officers of the two
armed forces have restored exchanges, and the China-U.S. military
relations have maintained a good momentum of improvement.
</P>
