<HEADLINE> Industrial Growth Drops to 5.5 Percent in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The manufacturing sector accounting for nearly four-fifth of
the total weight of index for industrial production (IIP)
registered a lower growth rate of 5.8 percent in May 2000 compared
to 8.9 percent in the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
The cumulative growth rate during the first two months of the
current fiscal year (April-May 2000) was marginally low at 5.5
percent as against 5.6 percent registered during April-May 1999,
the CSO said. 
</P>
