<HEADLINE> China's T-bond Market Fluctuates Narrowly on Wednesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 12 (Xinhua) -- China's T-bond trade kept
fluctuating narrowly on Wednesday, with the total trading value
expanding by 150 million yuan to 1.4 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Sources say that 009704, a 9.78 percent bond due 2007, lost
most to 143.50 yuan, a little below its five-day and ten-day
average prices and pushing the yield up 0.03 percentage points to
4.02 percent.
</P>
<P>
Bond 010004, the only bond with floating interest rate on the
market, picked up by 0.09 percent to 102.00 yuan with turnover
totaling 401 million yuan. The bond may withstand more selling
pressure to go up further, said Beijing-based financial advisory
company Homeway.
</P>
<P>
The remaining four bonds were flat during the trading day. The
quiet T-bond market is mainly due to the bullish stock markets,
Homeway analysts said.
</P>
<P>
The trade volume on three-day, seven-day, 14-day and 28-day
repo transactions contracted by 826 million yuan to 1.51 billion
yuan. Meanwhile, the interest rate on the three-day product rose 0.
13 percentage points to 4.02 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
