<HEADLINE> China's Fund Market Quiet on Wednesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 12 (Xinhua) -- China's securities investment fund
market fluctuated slightly on Wednesday, according to Homeway,
China's leading on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Among 22 funds that were traded at a discount, 9 funds rose, 8
remained unchanged and 5 dropped. But the turnover for each fund
moved within a small range.
</P>
<P>
Fund Jinyuan, which made its debut yesterday, opened high at
its ceiling price with active trading. But only 209,400 fund units
changed hands, with its daily turnover rate at less than 0.1
percent.
</P>
<P>
Affected by Fund Jinyuan, the other four restructured funds
also performed actively today, Homeway said. 
</P>
