<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Heat Wave Hits Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Beijing today reported a maximum
temperature of 40 degrees Celsius (104 Fahrenheit) again. This is
the second time that the capital city is hit by a heat wave since
July 1.
</P>
<P>
It was rare that such a high temperature hit Beijing twice
within two weeks, said Ding Deping, head of Beijing professional
meteorological station.
</P>
<P>
However, he added that it did not necessarily mean this summer
would be hotter than usual. The most scorching temperature in
Beijing in 1942 reached 42.6 degrees Celsius.
</P>
<P>
Statistics showed that temperatures of 13 days have surpassed
35 degrees Celsius since this June in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The average maximum temperatures in Beijing normally occur in
mid-July. 
</P>
</TEXT>
