<HEADLINE> Shanghai A-share Market Closes At Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 12 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Composite Index
closed at 1973.37 points on Wednesday, up 12.83 points or 0.65
percent, compared with the last close.
</P>
<P>
Total trading volume was 14.91 billion yuan (1.79 billion U.S.
dollars), 3.6 percent more than the previous session's 14.39
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
This is the second consecutive day when the market finished at
record highs, and analysts said that the announcement that the
government will support the development of software and integrated
circuit industries buoyed investor's confidence in the hi-tech
industries, according to Homeway, China's leading on-line
financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1.197 billion shares changed hands today and market
gainers outnumbered losers by 287 to 191, with the prices of
another 16 stocks unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Oriental Enterprise Co Ltd and Nanning Chemical Industry Co Ltd,
the firms that listed their stocks on the market today, were among
the top gainers. The former skyrocketed 198.88 percent to 18.68
yuan per share while the latter soared 172.26 percent to close at
12.66 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang Friendship (Group) Co Ltd, which has gene-related
projects, and Shanghai Tyre and Rubber Co Ltd were also among top
gainers. The former surged 10.03 percent to 17.99 yuan while the
latter jumped 10.02 percent to 11.97 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Dazhong Enterprise of Science and Technology Ltd was
the biggest loser today, with its price declining 8.31 percent to
end at 1.96 yuan per share.
</P>
<P>
The market is likely to try a new high tomorrow, Homeway
analysts said.  
</P>
