<HEADLINE> Chinese, U.S. Military Leaders on Taiwan issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Evasion of the One-China principle
has no way out, and Taiwan issue can not and will not be delayed
indefinitely, said Chinese Defense Minister Chi Haotian here today.
</P>
<P>
"Sino-U.S. relationship is facing opportunities and problems as
well, and the most important and sensitive of the problems is the
Taiwan issue," Chi said in a meeting with U.S. Defense Secretary
William Cohen.
</P>
<P>
Pointing out that the U.S. side has promised for many times
its adherence to the One-China policy, observance of the three
Sino-U.S. joint communiques and the "three-no" commitment, Chi
urged the U.S. to honor its commitment and not to give the Taiwan
authorities a wrong signal.
</P>
<P>
Reunification of China and to oppose splitting activities have
been an irreversible trend and common aspiration of the entire
Chinese people, which has also been favored by people all over the
world, Chi stressed.
</P>
<P>
Cohen said that the U.S. side has fully realized the importance
and sensitivity of the Taiwan issue, and it will adhere to the One-
China policy and abide by the three joint communiques between the
two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
