<HEADLINE> China Urges U.S. to Abandon NMD </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 12 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese officer today
urged the United States to treat seriously the strong appeal of
the international community and abandon the National Missile
Defense (NMD) at the earliest time.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Defense Minister Chi Haotian reiterated the stance of
the Chinese government in a meeting with U.S. Defense Secretary
William Cohen here this morning.
</P>
<P>
Peace and development are the trend of the time, and the world
is moving toward ease, Chi said.
</P>
<P>
However, the NMD system will have a negative impact on the
efforts for global strategic equilibrium and stability,
international arms control, disarmament and non-proliferation, he
stressed. 
</P>
