<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Turkish Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 12 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading Turkish newspapers on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Hurriyet:
</P>
<P>
-- Turkish President Ahmet Necdet Sezer, who paid a visit to
Azerbaijan, met Azeri President Haydar Aliyev in Baku on Tuesday.
Following the meeting, Aliyev said the two sides has agreed over
the construction of the Baku-Ceyhan oil pipeline in the first
phase.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Daily News:
</P>
<P>
-- Turkish Foreign Minister Ismail Cem complained on Tuesday
that the European Union (EU) has not yet provided a financial
package for Turkey since its being accepted as an EU candidate.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks in his meetings with the EU ambassadors in
Ankara.
</P>
<P>
Yenibinyil:
</P>
<P>
-- Turkey has started giving signals that it will change its
stand toward the issue of water with Syria as Basar al-Assad, the
new leader of the country, took office.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said the expected visit of Basar to Turkey will
represent new possibilities to solve the water issue between the
two countries and improve bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Milliyet:
</P>
<P>
-- Turkish Prime Minister Bulent Ecevit Tuesday approved an
appeal by the Health Ministry to declare a four-day holiday
starting Thursday, because of the record-breaking hot weather
currently hitting the country.
</P>
<P>
It was the first time in the country to declare a holiday
because of heat. Meteorologists said the highest temperatures on
Thursday will be 40 degrees Celsius in Ankara, Izmir and Adana, 35
degree Celsius in Istanbul. 
</P>
