<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST -- Romania hopes to revive its flagging trade with
Russia, Prime Minister Mugur Isarescu said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with Russia's State Duma Speaker Gennady Seleznyov, he
said Romania's  exports to Russia plunged year by year, recording
an aggregated trade deficit of 430 million U.S. dollars. The
figure accounted for one third of Romania's total trade deficit.
(Romania-Russia-Visit)
</P>
