<HEADLINE> ITF Strips Neiland of Aussie Open Prize Money </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Latvia's Larisa Neiland has been
stripped of the prize money she won at the 1999 Australian Open
after testing positive for caffeine.
</P>
<P>
Neiland, winner of six Grand Slam doubles and mixed doubles
titles, will have to return the $15,134 she received for reaching
the doubles quarterfinals at the Australian Open with Spain's
Arantxa Sanchez-Vicario, the International Tennis Federation (ITF)
said in its weekly news bulletin.
</P>
<P>
Neiland, 33, tested positive for the stimulant at the
tournament but the announcement of her punishment was delayed
until the appeals procedure had run its course. 
</P>
