<HEADLINE> Xinjiang Holds Tourism Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, July 12 (Xinhua) -- The week-long women's national
beach volleyball match opened at Jinshatan Beach in northwest
China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region today.
</P>
<P>
This is part of the activities for the month-long tourism
festival being held at the Mongolian Autonomous Prefecture of
Bayingolin in Xinjiang. Other activities include performance,
evening gala, trade fair, symposium and garment show.
</P>
<P>
Known as the largest prefecture in China, Bayingolin is
endowed with Baghrash Lake, the largest inland fresh water lake in
China; the Tarim River, China's longest inland river; and Bayan
Bulag swan preserve, the largest of its kind in China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
