<DOCNO> XIE20000712.0217 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Economic News Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Economic news briefs:
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Helps Ningxia Develop Economy
</P>
<P>
Economic cooperation between Shanghai, China's leading
industrial and commercial city, and the Ningxia Hui Autonomous
Region has greatly promoted the economic development in this
Muslim-inhabited region in northwest China.
</P>
<P>
The two sides recently signed 29 agreements on high-tech
development, upgrading of traditional industries, biological
projects, urban construction, trade and tourism, involving a total
investment of 1.97 billion yuan (237 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has helped Ningxia develop economy since the
autonomous region was founded in 1958. Shanghai has established
relations of cooperation with more than 100 industrial and
commercial businesses, scientific research institutes, health care
centers and hospitals in Ningxia since reforms started in the late
1970s.
</P>
<P>
 Project to Divert River Water Into Xi'an
</P>
<P>
A project to divert water from the Heihe River into Xi'an,
capital of northwest China's Shaanxi province, is expected to be
completed next year.
</P>
<P>
Xi'an is one of the Chinese cities suffering from serious water
shortages. The city's daily water demand stands at 900,000 cubic
meters.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the project has provided 1.02 billion cubic
meters of water for Xi'an since it became operational in 1987.
</P>
<P>
The second phase, upon completion, will supply 1.72 million
cubic meters of water for the city every day.
</P>
<P>
The project can also supply 123 million cubic meters of water
for 24,666 hectares of farmland.
</P>
<P>
 China to Build Monitoring System for Grain Information
</P>
<P>
China plans to set up a monitoring system to keep a close eye
on grain prices and related information in major cities, large-
scale grain enterprises and grain production bases, according to
the State Grain Reserve Administration.
</P>
<P>
The system will consist of more than 200 monitoring stations
built in 31 provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions. The
stations are responsible for collecting latest grain prices, grain
policies of central and local governments, important speeches made
by state leaders, and other related information.
</P>
<P>
The project is aimed at promoting the reform in grain
circulation, strengthening state control over grain production and
helping farmers adjust their growing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
