<HEADLINE> Procurators to Compete for Vacant Posts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 12 (Xinhua) -- The Supreme People's Procuratorate
(SPP) has decided to select candidates for high positions in the
SPP through competition.
</P>
<P>
A SPP spokesman said there are 18 vacant posts at bureau-
director level and 130 at section-chief level in the SPP. The
vacancies are open to procurators in the SPP itself, and those
from procuratorates in Beijing as well.
</P>
<P>
Candidates are expected to register for the competition or be
recommended by other people, make speeches and oral defenses, and
be subject to assessment by the masses and examination by the
superior department.
</P>
<P>
It was reported earlier that China will organize national
examinations to select procurators, in a bid to improve the
competence of procurators.
</P>
<P>
According to the SPP, there are about 7,200 vacancies of
procurators across the country, which will be filled with those
who pass the national exams.  
