<HEADLINE> Yahoo! Reports Huge Profits, Sales for 2nd Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Yahoo! Inc., the leading
consumer Internet portal, on Tuesday reported sharp increases in
its second quarter earnings and revenues.
</P>
<P>
For the three months ended June 30, the Santa Clara, California-
based company earned net income of 65 million U.S. dollars,
compared with a loss of 263,000 dollars in the year-ago period.
</P>
<P>
Excluding acquisition and other one-time charges, the company
earned 74.9 million dollars, compared to 27.1 million dollars in
the same period a year ago.
</P>
<P>
Sales rose to 270.1 million dollars from 128.6 million dollars
the year before. Page views, a key measure of traffic to Yahoo!'s
network of online properties, rose about 9 percent to an average
680 million per day in June, from 625 million in March.
</P>
<P>
Other highlights of the quarter include Yahoo! building its
worldwide network to 156 million users worldwide, including 20
million in Japan alone.
</P>
<P>
Yahoo! delivered 4.4 billion messages on its e-mail services in
June, up from 3.6 billion in March, the company said, adding that
it delivered more than 13 million hours of streamed audio and
video programming in June, up from 11 million in March. 
</P>
</TEXT>
