<HEADLINE> New Zealand's Paper Mill to Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, July 12 (Xinhua) -- New Zealand's industrial Giant
Carter Holt Harvey has decided to mothball its Mataura Paper Mill
in the Southern part of the South Island from August 18,
Television New Zealand reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Carter Holt Harvey said since 1995 the market prices for
commodity papers such as copy paper have continued to trend
downward, and the mill has been making a loss for the past four
years.
</P>
<P>
The mill will remain idle until such time as market conditions
significantly improve to justify resuming operations, it added.
</P>
<P>
The mothballing will result in a redundancy of 155 people.
</P>
<P>
New Zealand Employment and Social Services Minister Steve
Maharey said in a Wednesday's government press release that he is
"sad to learn of the decision" and New Zealand departments
concerned will be actively assisting affected staff to find new
employment opportunities. 
