<HEADLINE> 50 People Die of Mushroom Poisoning in Ukraine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, July 11 (Xinhua) -- About 50 people, among them 11 were
children, have died of mushroom poisoning since the spring of this
year, the Ukrainian Interfax news agency quoted the Health
Ministry as saying on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 589 cases of mushroom poisoning have taken place in
the country since this year, with the worst place being
Donetskaya, where 24 people have died in 120 reported cases.
While in the Lugansk region, there have been 16 deaths in 166
cases.
</P>
<P>
With increasing mushroom poisoning and rising death toll, the
Health Ministry has sent medical groups to affected areas and
provided medical aid.
</P>
<P>
Last year, 200 mushroom poisoning cases were reported, with
only one death. 
