<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Taufik Haunted by Back Injury </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia Open defending champion
Taufik Hidayat may lose his chance to retain his title as he is
suffering from a back injury.
</P>
<P>
Michael Triangel, the official doctor of the Badminton
Association of Indonesia (PBSI), said that Taufuk had an X ray but
the results "were not very good".
</P>
<P>
"I recommended him to have another X ray tomorrow (Wednesday)
and there should be a result in the afternoon. Taufik has been
complaining about the injury and I think it is the old one that
reoccurs from time to time," he was quoted by the Jakarta Post
Wednesday as saying.
</P>
<P>
Michael said Taufik's injury was most likely muscle strain.
</P>
<P>
"But we should wait first and look at tomorrow's X ray to
decided if it really is muscle strain or if the injury has got
something to do with his bones," he added.
</P>
<P>
Taufik visited orthopedic specialist Dr. Chaehab on Tuesday
morning as the doctor was unavailable the day before.
</P>
<P>
Michael said if Taufik injured his back, he would have to take
a month's rest and would not be able to compete in the Indonesia
Open.
</P>
<P>
Separately, PBSI secretary-general Leo Chandra Wiranata said he
hoped Taufik was not suffering from a serious injury.
</P>
<P>
"I saw his practice this morning (Tuesday) at the Indonesian
Badminton Center in Cipayung, East Jakarta, and I didn't see
anything wrong with the way he was playing. I hope his complaint
was not about anything serious. After practice, Taufik went to
visit Dr. Chaehab. Maybe we will need to have a second opinion on
his injury," he said.
</P>
<P>
Leo said if Taufik was injured, PBSI would not force him to
compete in the Indonesia Open as the organization prefers the 19-
year-old shuttler to concentrate on the Olympic Games in Sydney in
September.
</P>
<P>
"He's one of our backbone players in the Olympics and he has a
great chance to reach the finals. Let's hope he's fine," he said.
</P>
<P>
Taufik, who is a recipient of the Olympics Solidarity
scholarship, won the Indonesia Open title in Bali last year after
beating senior Budi Santoso in the all Indonesian final. 
</P>
