<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Exports of Machinery &AMP; Electric Items Augmented </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Qingdao, a major industrial city
in east China's Shandong Province, has seen for the first time
machinery and electric products on top of the trade items.
</P>
<P>
The city exported 578 million U.S. dollars worth of machinery
and electric items from January to May this year, a big rise of 58.
1 percent on a yearly basis, and 19.9 percentage points higher
than the average growth rate of trade.
</P>
<P>
Machinery and electric products account for 26.3 percent of
local exports in the five-month period.
</P>
<P>
Local name-brand household-appliance enterprises like Hai'er,
Hisense, and Aukma, play an important role in local exports and
account for one-third of local machinery and electric exports.
</P>
<P>
Hai'er has funded six plants overseas and 68 percent of its
household appliances have been exported to many developed
countries, including America and European countries.
</P>
<P>
Textile exports rose 25 percent year-on-year to nearly 100
million U.S. dollars during the first five months of this year,
with the trade volume for chemicals growing by 43 percent to 38
million U.S. dollars and that for machinery climbing 40 percent to
35 million U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
