<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar Seizes Over One Ton of Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 12 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar authorities seized a
total of 1,044 kilos of narcotic drugs in the first five months of
this year, according to the latest statistics of the country's
Central Committee for Drug Abuse Control.
</P>
<P>
The seizure, made by army units, police and the customs,
includes 678.4 kilos of opium, 20.2 kilos of heroin and 330.75
kilos of marijuana as well as 3,999 liters of precursor chemicals
and 7.358 million tablets of stimulant drugs.
</P>
<P>
During the five-month period, the authorities exposed a total
of 1,586 drug-related cases, punishing 2,170 drug offenders.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, there remains 89,500 hectares of poppy cultivation
in the country.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Myanmar is implementing a 255-million-U.S.-dollar 15-
year drug elimination plan which covers 51 cultivating and
producing townships.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, in 1999 the Myanmar
authorities seized 1,447.55 kilos of opium, 272.94 kilos of heroin,
274.48 kilos of marijuana, 278.97 liters of phensedyl, 262,542.5
liters of precursor chemicals as well as 28.75 million tablets of
stimulant drugs, destroying 12 heroin refineries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
