<HEADLINE> Iraq Wins Group-4 of Asian U-19 Football Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Iraqis emerged as unbeaten group
champions to reach the finals of the 32nd Asian Youth Under-19
Football Championship, making a 1-1 tamed draw with host
Bangladesh Tuesday in Rajshahi, a northwestern city of Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
In Tuesday's last group match, both teams secured seven points
each, but the Asian titan Iraq clinched the group title by better
goal difference. Iraq scored 14 goals in total conceding one
against Bangladesh who scored six conceding two goals.
</P>
<P>
Iraq will now play in the 12-team final round scheduled for
October in their neighbouring Iran, according to the United News
of Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
In Tuesday's another match, Nepal and Maldives shared point in
their last engagement of the group-4 qualifiers, which ended in a
goal-less draw. 
