<HEADLINE> Largest Daily-Use Chemicals JV Set up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 12 (Xinhua) -- A Sino-U.S. joint venture to
produce chemicals for daily use, believed to be the largest of its
kind in China, went into operation Monday in Yangzhou in east
China's Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture, the Colgate Sanxiao Co. Ltd. is a product of
joint effort of the U.S.'s Colgate Palmolive Company and the local
Sanxiao Group, which is China's largest toothbrush manufacturer.
</P>
<P>
It involves a total investment of 15 million U.S. dollars, with
Colgate Palmolive contributing 70 percent of the shares. Palmolive
is a world-renowned daily-use chemicals giant.
</P>
<P>
The new firm will manufacture a wide range of products,
including toothbrush, toothpaste, soap, shampoo, bath lotion,
cosmetics and detergents.
</P>
<P>
Colgate Sanxiao announced that it will introduce management
methods from multinationals and intends to increase its output by
20 percent annually in coming years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
