<HEADLINE> Chinese Education to Receive More Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 12 (Xinhua) -- China will spend more on distance
learning, training of college teachers, laboratory building and
university-based technological parks, China Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
Yet, officials from the Ministry of Education did not disclose
how much would be spent, the English-language newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The China Education and Research Network, an internet link for
700 universities and research institutes across the country, will
begin using higher speed transmission lines later this year to
offer more opportunities for young people and adults.
</P>
<P>
The ministry also encourages college teachers to seek
technological breakthroughs that are closely related to the
country's development.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the plan will support over 2,500 research
programs and finance 2,699 teachers, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The ministry will help major universities build more labs to
develop technologies in life sciences, biology, information
technology and new material science. 
</P>
