<HEADLINE> Fujimori Opens Amazonian Parliament Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Peruvian President Alberto Fujimori
opened Wednesday in Lima the Third Amazonian Parliament
Extraordinary Assembly with the attendance of delegates from its
eight member countries.
</P>
<P>
Fujimori said in his opening speech that the strengthening of
the Amazonian cooperation is necessary because it is "the most
indicated vehicle" for the defense and conservation of the
Amazonia.
</P>
<P>
Legislators from Bolivia, Brazil, Colombia, Ecuador, Guayana,
Peru, Surinam and Venezuela are attending the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Peruvian president said that respect for national
sovereignty must be established "very clearly" in the development
of cooperation for the exploitation of the Amazonian region.
</P>
<P>
"It is necessary to make compatible the national interest of
our countries with the interests of the developed countries in the
protection of this resource (the Amazonia), which all of us
consider of world transcendence," said Fujimori.
</P>
<P>
Fujimori said that there are four topics that must be
considered about the Amazonia use: rational economic exploitation,
conservation of the biodiversity, development of the human
surroundings, and cooperation among the Amazonian countries.
</P>
<P>
The assembled delegates of the eight countries will discuss
issues related to actions directed to the progress and
preservation of the Amazonian natural resources.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
