<HEADLINE> Colombian Oil Output Drops Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Colombian oil production dropped
more than 14 percent during the first semester of this year
against the same period of 1999, according to data released
Wednesday by the Colombian Oil Enterprise (ECOPETROL).
</P>
<P>
The actual production was 710,350 barrels a day, 10.39 percent
below the official production estimate that foresaw an average of
792,700 barrels a day during the first six months of this year.
</P>
<P>
The output reduction forced Colombia to export 20.53 percent
less in volume of crude in the first five months of this year
against the same period o 1999.
</P>
<P>
Colombian oil production has shown a dropping trend for one
year and a half although it is expected to revert with the finding
of the El Boqueron (Tolima) field in the west of the country, and
other prospective findings.  
</P>
</TEXT>
