<HEADLINE> Foot and Mouth Disease Found in Northern Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Greek veterinarians have found
cases of the foot and mouth disease in the country's northern
prefecture of Evros and more bovines are expected to be killed as
a precautionary measure.
</P>
<P>
A total of eight herds of bovines in the Ainision Delta, near
the Greek-Turkish border, were found over the past two days with
clinical symptoms of the foot and mouth disease and some one
thousand bovines would be killed, the semi-official Athens News
Agency (ANA) reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Veterinarians believed that the foot and mouth disease was
transmitted from neighboring Turkey.
</P>
<P>
While great efforts were being made to restrict the disease to
the Delta region, intensive checks were being carried out with all
herds to detect any more outbreaks.
</P>
<P>
During 1994-1998, more than 150,000 animals were killed in
Thrace when a similar outbreak had occurred. 
</P>
</TEXT>
