<HEADLINE> Chilean Salmon, Trout Exports Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The fishing industry collected 483.2 million U.S. dollars in
the first five months of this year, while the returns from salmon
and trout exports amounted to 397.2 million dollars. This increase
can be attributed to the fact that the volumes exported have risen
in the first six months of the year by 23.2 percent, to a total of
95,539 tons.
</P>
<P>
Japan occupies the biggest amount of the Chilean exports. Sixty-
two percent of the total revenue of the industry came from that
country, meaning 299.4 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Second place goes to the United States, whose market
contributed 132.8 million dollars, 27.4 percent of the total,
followed by Brazil, Germany, and France.  
</P>
</TEXT>
