<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Rise On Tech Strength </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stock rose broadly
Wednesday after the Internet portal Yahoo! reported its better-
than-expected earnings in the second quarter later Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed up 56.57 at 10,783.76
in the fourth straight session.
</P>
<P>
The technology heavy Nasdaq composite index rose 143.17 at 4,
099.59, recovering all the losses of 66.78 points in the previous
two sessions.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were also higher. The Standard &AMP; Poor'
s 500 index rose 12.04 at 1,492.92.
</P>
<P>
Stocks rallied Wednesday after Yahoo!, the Internet giant,
reported after the close of session Tuesday that its second-
quarter earnings rose 11 cents a share, a penny better than the
Wall Street analysts' predication, quelling investor concerns
about profits of the net companies.
</P>
<P>
Yahoo!'s shares rose sharply, boosting the technology sector.
American Online and CMGI were also higher.
</P>
<P>
Financial stocks rose as well after the New York investment
bank PaineWebber agreed to be merged with Swiss banking group UBS.
PaineWebber, Lehman Brothers and Merrill Lynch rose.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index rose 1.23 at 661.13 and the American Stock
Exchange index rose 1.77 at 954.97. The Russell 2000 index of
smaller companies rose 10.51 at 540.25.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 4-to-3 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,739 up, 1,185 down and 478
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 994.63 million shares from 976.13
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
